    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1176406/" class="title-link">以理性解读疯狂：读《德国反犹史》</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1176406"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/pasternak/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1095661-1.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/pasternak/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">光荣与梦想</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2007-07-05"
      class="main-meta">2007-07-05 21:58:15</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1176406_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  翻看《德国反犹史》的过程，绝对是场异乎寻常的体验。对它的阅读，是理性应对疯狂，是良知面对罪恶。无论惊心动魄还是悲伤愤怒，都无以形容。正如本书作者费舍尔所言，这的确是个“让我神经崩溃的噩梦”。  这场人类历史上空前绝后惨绝人寰的大屠杀，几乎是一场梦魇，启蒙理想...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1176406/#comments">(16回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">7有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
